claim.claim-text:
8. An implantable medical device, comprising:
means for sensing a first signal over a first channel between a first combination of electrodes on the lead;
means for determining whether the first signal is representative of a potential failure in the lead;
means for obtaining a secondary indicator of heart condition; and
means for utilizing the secondary indicator to confirm an arrhythmia of the heart when the determining operation identifies the lead to include the potential failure.
